      "writtenOn": "2019-03-29T00:29:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "great question. digging through the code, i think that we explicitly shouldn\u0027t close it here -- i\u0027ll add a comment.\n\nStdinPipe adds pw to closeAfterWait: https://golang.org/src/os/exec/exec.go?s\u003d15650:15699#L534\n\nand then Start appears to close everything in closeAfterWait if it encounters an error: https://golang.org/src/os/exec/exec.go?s\u003d10716:10743#L341\n\n(actually, this is no longer relevant now that args are marshaled beforehand)",
      "parentUuid": "aff640ee_2d93e23c",
      "revId": "7240efb5fc74d23c6c52c1528cc85e64dc3d2ede",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c62cc674_5f301ded",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/runner/bundles.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
