      "writtenOn": "2019-03-29T00:29:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "thanks for suggesting this. i\u0027d thought about it earlier, but believed that i needed to wait to close stdin until after i got the process\u0027s session id. but that was before i realized that the session id always matches the PID, and and i now realize that (i think) it\u0027s also the case that the process entry remains present until wait() is called.\n\nso i\u0027ve simplified this as you suggest. simpler error handling is usually better. :-)",
      "parentUuid": "c62cc674_5f301ded",
